ARCHITECTURE
  Lifecycle:      systemd user service (auto-start, auto-restart)
  Toggle IPC:     qs ipc call spotlight toggle
  On-close:       Daemon stays alive (~2MB RSS overhead vs cold launch)
  Split:          1 monolithic QML → 7 focused QML files (backend + 6 UI components)
  Imports:        Each new file imports only the QML modules it needs
  Data flow:      All UI components receive `required property var backend` (the Scope)
                  for state reads and function calls. No deep property threading.
  Theme system:   2 theme JS objects (`_macosTheme`, `_win95Theme`) with 75+ tokens
                  each (colors, radii, borders, fonts, animation params, structural
                  flags). 60+ tokens exposed as `readonly property` on root Scope.
                  Components reference all visuals via `backend.<tokenName>` —
                  zero hardcoded colors in component files.
                  Switch via: `backend.applyTheme("macos"|"win95")` from QML,
                  `/theme macos|win95` search command, or
                  `qs ipc call spotlight themeMacos` / `themeWin95`.
                  Persisted in spotlight-data/theme.json, loaded on each open.

